maml:description.maml:para: Gets user information from the google apps domain

The Get-GDataUser cmdlet gets information about users from a google apps domain.
You have to specify -UserService for the cmdlet to be able to connect to the domain.
Without the -ID parameter you will get information about all the users on the specified domain.
By default, Get-GDataUser returns an object that has detailed information about the user/users.
Insert the object returned from the cmdlet Get-GDataUserService. It specifies which domain to get the userinformation from.
Specify the username of the user to fetch information about.
